<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-04T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-04T14:00:00-05:00" n="244" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d244">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1901</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PTN1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-04T15:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 4,
                                            1918, 3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1395. Your 1669, May 28, 3 p.m.<note n="2" xml:id="d244fn2"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_175">p.
                                    175</ref>.</note> Deeply interested in program of League for
                                Regeneration of Russia with which this Government, in the main,
                                agrees. Would be pleased to have the league communicate
                                confidentially details of its plan of action, for consideration.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>